com.bigdata.blueprints

Class BigdataGraphBulkLoad

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bigdata.blueprints.BigdataGraph
      • com.bigdata.blueprints.BigdataGraphBulkLoad
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IChangeLog, com.tinkerpop.blueprints.Graph, com.tinkerpop.blueprints.TransactionalGraph

    public class BigdataGraphBulkLoad
extends BigdataGraph
implements com.tinkerpop.blueprints.TransactionalGraph, IChangeLog
    Simple bulk loader that will insert graph data without any consistency checking (won't check for duplicate vertex or edge identifiers). Currently does not overwrite old property values, but we may need to change this.

    Implements IChangeLog so that we can report a mutation count.

    Author:
    mikepersonick

      • transactionPrepare

        public void transactionPrepare()
        Description copied from interface: IChangeLog
        Message issued when preparing for a commit. The next message will be either IChangeLog.transactionCommited(long) or IChangeLog.transactionAborted().

        Note: The listener will have observed all updates by the time this message is generated. Thus, this message can be used to validate post-conditions for the transaction.

        Specified by:
        transactionPrepare in interface IChangeLog
